  <!-- PROGRAMS -->
  <section id="programs">
    <h2>Example Training Programs for Teens</h2>
    <p>These sample programs assume you are healthy and cleared for physical activity, and they prioritize full‑body strength, good movement patterns, and gradual progression 2–3 days per week.</p>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Beginner: 2‑Day Full‑Body Program (Weeks 1–4)</h3>
      <p>Perform each workout 2 days per week on non‑consecutive days (for example, Monday and Thursday), starting with only bodyweight or very light weights and focusing on slow, controlled reps.</p>

      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Exercise</th>
              <th>Sets × Reps</th>
              <th>Rest</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Bodyweight squat</td>
              <td>3 × 10–12</td>
              <td>60–90 s</td>
              <td>Keep heels down, chest up, and knees tracking over toes. [web:32]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Push‑up (elevated if needed)</td>
              <td>3 × 6–10</td>
              <td>60–90 s</td>
              <td>Body in straight line; lower chest between hands, not head first. [web:32]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Dumbbell or band row</td>
              <td>3 × 10–12</td>
              <td>60–90 s</td>
              <td>Pull toward lower ribs, pause, and squeeze shoulder blades. [web:32]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Reverse lunge</td>
              <td>2–3 × 8 each leg</td>
              <td>60–90 s</td>
              <td>Step back, drop straight down, front knee over ankle. [web:32]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Front plank</td>
              <td>3 × 20–30 s</td>
              <td>45–60 s</td>
              <td>Keep straight line from ears to ankles without sagging. [web:32][web:35]</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
      <h3>Intermediate: 3‑Day Strength Program (Weeks 5–8)</h3>
      <p>Once technique is solid and you can complete beginner workouts comfortably, you can move to 3 days per week, splitting lower‑body, upper‑body, and full‑body sessions.</p>

      <h4 style="font-size:0.95rem; margin-top:0.75rem;">Day 1 – Lower Body & Core</h4>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Exercise</th>
              <th>Sets × Reps</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Goblet squat</td>
              <td>3–4 × 8–10</td>
              <td>Hold dumbbell at chest, keep elbows inside knees at bottom. [web:32]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Romanian deadlift (dumbbells)</td>
              <td>3 × 8–10</td>
              <td>Push hips back with flat back, feel stretch in hamstrings. [web:31]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Walking lunges</td>
              <td>3 × 10 steps each leg</td>
              <td>Short, controlled steps; no “slamming” knee into floor. [web:32][web:35]</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Side plank</td>
              <td>3 × 20–30 s per side</td>
              <td>Stack shoulders and hips, avoid sagging. [web:32]</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
