      <div class="form-list">
        <h3>Upper‑Body Technique Cues</h3>
        <ul>
          ><strong>Push‑ups / Pressing</strong>: Hands just outside shoulder‑width, elbows at about a 45° angle from your sides, not flared straight out. [web:32]</li>
          ><strong>Rows</strong>: Keep chest lifted, pull shoulder blade back and down before bending the elbow. [web:32]</li>
          ><strong>Overhead work</strong>: Only go overhead if you can raise arms without arching your low back; start with light dumbbells or bands. [web:32]</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top:1rem;">Safety Guidelines</h3>
        <ul>
          >Warm up 5–10 minutes before lifting with light cardio and dynamic movements. [web:32][web:38]</li>
          >Start with bodyweight or very light weights; add load slowly over weeks, not days. [web:31][web:34]</li>
          >Stop a set when technique breaks down, even if you could do more reps.</li>
          >Avoid “one‑rep max” testing until late teens and only with experienced coaching. [web:34][web:40]</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
